cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

This paper deals with the problem of segmenting an image based on a natural language expression, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end trainable recurrent and convolutional network model that jointly learns to process visual and linguistic information, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques to achieve the segmentation task, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval, as it aims to extract relevant information from the image based on the natural language expression, which is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
